<p>For the mean Cover-weighted FQI per plot, we first calculated Cover-weighted Mean 
 <italic>C</italic> as follows: 
 <inline-formula id="pone.0241061.e001">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0241061.e001.jpg" id="pone.0241061.e001g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M1">
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msubsup>
        <mo stretchy="true">∑</mo>
        <mrow>
         <mi>i</mi>
         <mo>=</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mi>S</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msubsup>
       <mrow>
        <msub>
         <mrow>
          <mi>c</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
        <msub>
         <mrow>
          <mi>p</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
       </mrow>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msubsup>
        <mo stretchy="true">∑</mo>
        <mrow>
         <mi>i</mi>
         <mo>=</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mi>S</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msubsup>
       <mrow>
        <msub>
         <mrow>
          <mi>p</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
       </mrow>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>, where 
 <italic>c</italic> is the C-value of species 
 <italic>i</italic>, and 
 <italic>p</italic> is the percent cover of species 
 <italic>i</italic> within the plot, for all 
 <italic>S</italic> species within the plot. We then used this Cover-weighted Mean 
 <italic>C</italic> in the calculation of FQI, as above.
</p>
